    "translation":{"eng":"Day and night, my heart burns in the blazing poisonous fire of the threefold miseries of material existence. Thus, my body repeatedly falls unconscious. My senses subjugated by the cardinal vices [of lust, anger, greed, etc.,] I have forgotten the lotus feet of Śrī Gaurāṅga and remain averse to that great treasure."}},{
